==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Patten
<hw>Pat"ten</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>patin</ets> a
high-heeled shoe, fr. <ets>patte</ets> paw, foot. Cf. <er>Panton</er>,
<er>Patt⟦eacute⟧</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A clog or sole of wood,
usually supported by an iron ring, worn to raise the feet from the wet
or the mud.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>patten</qex> now supports each frugal dame.</q>
<rj><qau>Gay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A stilt.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pattened</ent>⟦br⟧
